        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-17T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-17T08:00:00-05:00" n="835" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d835">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">871.6363/7–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 835<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KGF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d835fn1">The gist of this message was included in telegram
                        No. 65 of July 19 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 800.00
                        Summaries/7–1945).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-17T16:00:00+03:00">July 17, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2597. By letter to <persName corresp="#p_V7">Vyshinski</persName> of July 11,
                    British Ambassador<note n="2" xml:id="d835fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KSAC1">Sir Archibald Clark Kerr</persName>.</note>
                    stated British Government could not accept Soviet Government <pb facs="0933" n="739" xml:id="pg_739"/> views expressed in February 26 Foreign Office note
                    on removal oil field equipment from Rumania. (To <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>, repeated Bucharest 91, London 368) <persName corresp="#p_CK2">Clark Kerr</persName> protested continued Soviet requisitioning and removal
                    British equipment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KGF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
